Package com.github.seqware.queryengine.model

Provides the classes that the RESTful API will interact with.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
Atom<T extends Atom> Implements core functionality that is shared by all classes that require tags.
Group A Group of users that may share ACL permissions
Molecule<T extends Molecule> Defines core functionality that is shared by classes that are controlled by permissions and are atoms
Plugin An Plugin object groups pluginrun events that are created by software suites or related tools.
QueryFuture<ReturnType> This interface sketches out the result that might be returned from a asynchronous query.
QueryInterface This interface allows users to access queries that are built into the query engine, as well as install/un-install plug-ins that allow the user to perform additional annotation and/or other operations (in other words, this handles the R operations from CRUD)).
Reference A reference is a particular build version such as "hg19" or "hg18".
ReferenceSet A ReferenceSet is a collection of references which are a collection of contigs and coordinates.
TagSet A set of Tag specifications

Package com.github.seqware.queryengine.model Description

Provides the classes that the RESTful API will interact with. All entities, especially features, should have a globally unique ID and should be versioned
